We are dedicated to integrating innovative technologies to enhance user experiences and promote efficiency across all service lines. Our company is committed to excellence, innovation, and eco-friendly practices to serve our customers and communities better. 2. We strive to empower individuals through cutting-edge technology and provide services that enhance quality of life, from healthcare to real estate. 3. Brand Values Innovation: We prioritize continuous service improvement through innovative solutions, particularly in Artificial Intelligence and emerging technologies. Customer Focus: Our customers are at the center of everything we do. We are not just committed to meeting their needs, but to understanding and exceeding their expectations, ensuring they always feel valued and important. Sustainability: We are not just dedicated, but deeply committed to eco-friendly operations, ensuring our services and products are designed with minimal environmental impact. This commitment is a part of our core values and something we strive to uphold every day. Integrity: We uphold transparency, fairness, and honesty in all our interactions, maintaining the highest ethical standards. Collaboration: We value the input and collaboration of our employees, partners, and clients to build better services and products. 4. Membership Partner Program Xandre offers tiered benefits to partners which includes varying levels of benefits, such as priority customer support, advanced analytics, and performance boosting tools. Membership Tiers & Benefits File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 5 of 14Bronze Free Property Listing: Showcase your property on the Xandre platform for immediate visibility. Direct Booking Management: Effortlessly manage reservations and bookings directly through your Xandre dashboard. Gold Everything in Silver, Plus: Service Listings: Maximize your exposure by showcasing your full range of offerings. These tools include: Featured Listings: Increase visibility by highlighting your listings on the Xandre homepage. Priority Placement: Get prioritized placement on search result pages to stand out from the crowd. Discount Offers: Attract more guests by creating exclusive deals and promotions. 11. Privacy Policy At Xandre LLC, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our customers' personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard information when you interact with our booking, real estate, e-commerce, artificial intelligence (AI), healthcare, rental car, XanPay, and Xandre Insurance services. By using our services, you agree to the terms of this policy. Information We Collect File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 6 of 14We collect various types of information from users across our service sectors, including personal information, usage data, and technical data. Personal Information Booking and Real Estate: Name, contact information (email, phone number), payment details, identification documents (where required), and travel or real estate preferences. E-commerce: Name, shipping and billing address, contact information, payment details, and purchase history. AI and Healthcare: Name, medical history (for healthcare services), healthcare preferences, and diagnostic data generated by our AI systems. Rental Cars: Name, driver's license details, payment information, rental history, and preferences. XanPay: Payment information, transaction history, and billing details. Xandre Insurance: Name, contact details, insurance policy information, claims history, and health or property data (for tailored policies). Technical and Usage Data Device information (IP address, browser type, operating system) Usage patterns and interaction data across our platforms and services Cookies and tracking technologies to enhance user experience Location Data We may collect and use location data for certain services, such as car rentals, where GPS tracking is needed for vehicle security or user safety. How We Use Your Information We use our collected information to provide, maintain, and improve our services. Specific uses include: Service Delivery: To process bookings, real estate transactions, e-commerce purchases, AI- driven healthcare diagnostics, car rentals, payments through XanPay, and insurance policy issuance. Customer Support: To respond to inquiries, provide customer service, and resolve issues. Personalization: To tailor services to your preferences, such as personalized travel recommendations or healthcare solutions using AI technology. File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 7 of 14Security: To verify identity, prevent fraud, and secure transactions. Marketing and Promotions: With your consent, we may send promotional materials or advertisements related to Xandre LLC services, including new products or offers. Compliance: To meet legal obligations, such as adhering to regulatory requirements for financial services, healthcare data protection, and insurance policies. Sharing Your Information Xandre LLC may share your personal information with third parties under the following circumstances: Service Providers: We may share data with trusted third-party vendors who assist in providing our services, such as payment processors, real estate agents, healthcare professionals, and vehicle maintenance providers. Business Partners: We may partner with businesses that provide complementary services, such as car rental partnerships or co-branded insurance products. Legal Compliance: We may disclose information to government authorities or regulatory bodies when required by law, for legal claims, or to prevent fraud or illegal activity. Mergers or Acquisitions: Customer data may be transferred as part of a business merger, acquisition, or sale, subject to the applicable privacy standards. Your Privacy Rights Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data: Access and Correction: You have the right to access the personal data we hold about you and to request corrections or updates to your information. Data Portability: You can request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format. Deletion: You may request the deletion of your personal information where legally permissible. Objection and Restriction: You can object to or request restrictions on specific data uses, including marketing communications. Withdraw Consent: You can withdraw your consent to the use of your personal information for marketing at any time. To exercise your privacy rights, please contact us using the information below. Without your explicit consent, we do not sell or rent personal information to third parties for marketing purposes. File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 8 of 1412. Services Xandre LLC offers a variety of services including: Booking Services: We provide a user-friendly platform for efficient and eco-conscious booking solutions. Real Estate: Our real estate services offer buyers and sellers reliable and transparent assistance with eco-friendly housing options. E-commerce: We support businesses by providing sustainable and innovative e-commerce platforms. Artificial Intelligence: We use AI to enhance the functionality and effectiveness of our services, improving user experience and optimizing processes. Healthcare Services: Xandre LLC connects individuals with essential healthcare services, from nursing and driver assistance to elderly care, ensuring comprehensive and compassionate care. 13. Booking Services Rental Cars Xandre LLC will soon launch a rental car service designed to offer our customers eco-friendly, reliable transportation options. This service will feature: A selection of electric and hybrid vehicles to minimize environmental impact. Convenient, user-friendly booking platforms integrated with our existing systems. Flexible rental options for short-term and long-term needs. Enhanced customer support and seamless connectivity with our AI-driven platforms to ensure a personalized experience. 14. Xandre Insurance To complement our growing portfolio, Xandre LLC will introduce Xandre Insurance, a comprehensive service offering tailored insurance packages for individuals and businesses. Key features include: Coverage options for healthcare, vehicles (including our rental cars), real estate, and more. AI-driven risk assessment to provide personalized, cost-effective policies. Sustainable and socially responsible investment strategies for our insurance products. Streamlined claims processes to ensure fast, transparent, and hassle-free customer service. 18. XanPay We are also developing XanPay, a secure and efficient digital payment platform to streamline transactions across our services. XanPay will offer: A fast and secure method for processing payments in real estate, e-commerce, and healthcare services. Integration with digital wallets, cryptocurrency options, and traditional payment methods. Data security measures to protect personal information, with a focus on user-friendly interfaces. Rewards and loyalty programs for frequent users create additional value for our customers. 19. Artificial Intelligence (“Denga”) 20. Terms & Conditions These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern your access to and use of Xandre LLC’s services across booking, real estate, e-commerce, artificial intelligence (AI), healthcare, rental cars, XanPay, and Xandre Insurance sectors. By using our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree with these Terms, you must refrain from using our services. File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 10 of 14Acceptance of Terms By accessing or using Xandre LLC’s services, including but not limited to booking (flight, hotel, car rental, and home), real estate, e-commerce, AI-based services ("Denga"), healthcare, rental cars, XanPay, and Xandre Insurance, you agree to comply with these Terms and all applicable laws and regulations. These Terms may be updated occasionally, and continued use of the services constitutes acceptance of any changes. Eligibility To use our services, you must be at least 18 years old and have the legal capacity to enter into a binding agreement under applicable law. By accessing Xandre LLC’s services, you represent that you meet these requirements. User Accounts and Registration To access certain services offered by Xandre LLC, you may be required to create an account. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account information and all activities that occur under your account. You agree to provide accurate and current information when registering and to update such information as necessary. Account Security: You are responsible for keeping your login credentials secure. Xandre LLC is not liable for any unauthorized access to your account resulting from failing to secure your login information. Account Termination: Xandre LLC reserves the right to suspend or terminate your account if you violate these Terms or engage in fraudulent or illegal activity. Services Overview Booking Services Xandre LLC offers booking services for flights, hotels, flight + hotel packages, car rentals, and homes. These services are subject to availability, and Xandre LLC is not responsible for any changes, cancellations, or issues related to third-party providers. Cancellation Policies: Cancellation policies vary by service provider. You are responsible for reviewing and understanding the provider’s cancellation policy before booking. Payment Terms: All bookings are subject to full payment at the time of reservation, and any additional fees or taxes will be communicated during the booking process. Real Estate Services Xandre LLC facilitates real estate transactions, including buying, selling, and renting properties. All real estate transactions are conducted in compliance with applicable local laws and regulations. Liability Disclaimer: Xandre LLC is not responsible for the accuracy of property listings or File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 11 of 14the actions of third-party real estate agents or brokers. Due Diligence: Buyers and renters are encouraged to perform their due diligence before entering into any real estate transaction. E-commerce Platform Xandre LLC provides an e-commerce platform where partners can list and sell their products. As a user, you are responsible for ensuring that all transactions comply with applicable laws and that all products meet the quality and safety standards required by law. Partner Responsibilities: Partners must adhere to Xandre LLC’s guidelines on product listing, pricing, shipping, and returns. Xandre LLC reserves the right to remove products or partners that do not comply with these guidelines. User Transactions: Xandre LLC is not liable for disputes between users and sellers, but we provide a mediation service to resolve issues. Artificial Intelligence ("Denga") Our AI services are designed to enhance user experiences through personalized recommendations, data analysis, and advanced decision-making processes. Accuracy of Data: While Xandre LLC strives to provide accurate AI-driven insights, we do not guarantee the accuracy or reliability of information generated by our AI systems. Users are responsible for making informed decisions based on the provided data. Ethical Use of AI: Xandre LLC is committed to the ethical use of AI. Any misuse of AI technologies, such as manipulation or fraudulent activities, will result in immediate termination of services. Healthcare Services Xandre LLC’s healthcare services provide various AI-driven solutions, including virtual healthcare, diagnostics, and patient management tools. Medical Disclaimer: Xandre LLC does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. The information provided through our platform is intended to support, not replace, the relationship between you and your healthcare provider. Data Privacy: Healthcare data is protected under strict confidentiality measures in compliance with data protection laws. Refer to our Privacy Policy for more details. Rental Cars Xandre LLC offers eco-friendly car rental services, including electric and hybrid vehicles. Users are responsible for returning vehicles in the same condition they were rented. Rental Terms: The rental agreement will be specified at the time of booking, and it will File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 12 of 14include rental periods, mileage limits, and additional fees (such as fuel charges or damages). Liability: Users are responsible for any damage to the vehicle during the rental period and must comply with all traffic laws. XanPay (Payment System) Xandre LLC’s XanPay is a secure digital payment platform that supports transactions for services across all sectors. Transaction Security: All XanPay transactions are encrypted and protected with industry- standard security measures. Dispute Resolution: Any disputes regarding payments will be handled in accordance with our dispute resolution procedures outlined in the Payment Services Agreement. Xandre Insurance Xandre LLC provides tailored insurance solutions for healthcare, vehicles, and real estate. Insurance policies are subject to underwriting and approval processes. Policy Terms: Each insurance product is governed by specific terms and conditions. Users are responsible for reading and understanding their policy before making a purchase. Claims: Claims must be submitted according to the procedures outlined in the policy documentation. Xandre LLC is not liable for rejected or delayed claims resulting from failure to follow these procedures. Fees and Payments All payments for Xandre LLC services must be made through approved methods, including XanPay. Pricing and additional fees (such as taxes or service charges) will be communicated during the transaction process. Late Payments: Failure to make timely payments may result in suspension or termination of services. Refunds: Refund policies vary depending on the service and will be outlined in the specific terms for each service. Intellectual Property All content, software, trademarks, logos, and materials on Xandre LLC’s platform are owned by or licensed to Xandre LLC and are protected by applicable intellectual property laws. Users may not copy, distribute, or modify any of these materials without prior written consent from Xandre LLC. User Conduct File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 13 of 14You agree to use Xandre LLC’s services lawfully and refrain from: Engaging in any fraudulent or illegal activities. Misusing the platform, including unauthorized access to data or AI systems. Violating the rights of others, including intellectual property and privacy rights. Limitation of Liability Xandre LLC is not liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the platform or services, including but not limited to loss of data, loss of revenue, or property damage. Third-Party Providers: Xandre LLC is not responsible for the actions, omissions, or errors of third-party providers, including real estate agents, healthcare professionals, or vehicle rental partners. Governing Law These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Insert Jurisdiction]. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of Xandre LLC’s services will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in [Insert Jurisdiction]. Termination Xandre LLC reserves the right to suspend or terminate your access to our services at any time, without notice, if you violate these Terms or engage in illegal or unethical conduct. Contact Information For questions or concerns regarding these Terms and Conditions, please contact us at: Email: Phone: [Insert Contact Number] Address: [Insert Company Address] This Terms and Conditions document reflects Xandre LLC’s commitment to transparency, user protection, and compliance with industry standards across our booking, real estate, e-commerce, AI, healthcare, rental cars, XanPay, and Xandre Insurance services. Corporate Social Responsibility All employees at Xandre LLC are expected to: Uphold the company's core values and adhere to ethical and legal standards. File: Xandre_Brand_Guide_RAG.txt Page 14 of 14Ensure transparency and integrity in interactions with clients and partners. Commit to professional growth and continuous improvement. Foster a collaborative and inclusive work environment. Support eco-friendly initiatives within and outside of the workplace. AI Knowledge
